I have tried keygens that would only work if you changed the date on your computer to 2010. I have tried them all and i am telling you that this one WORKS! You just have to do it a different way...

Follow the instructions until he says "If You are using Adobe Master Collection CS5.5,
Then Open Adobe Acrobat X Pro, When asked for activation,
search for Adobe Design Premium CS5.5 on the list, copy key and activate.
Then Open Adobe Audition CS5.5, When asked for activation,
search for Adobe Production Premium CS5.5 on the list, copy key and activate."

Neither Adobe Design Premium CS5.5 nor Adobe Production Premium CS5.5 are on the list so you have to individually go through the adobe program list and use the keygen to generate serials for each program individually and it works like a charm!

Just remember not to enter your adobe id if you have one and don't allow adobe to randomly see how you are using their programs or whatever when they ask.
